Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
get_snap_grid_info(25.10)                            get_snap_grid_info(25.10)

Name
       get_snap_grid_info - Gets information on the current snap grid settings

Syntax
        get_snap_grid_info

       [-help]

       [-origin]

       [-pitch_x]

       [-pitch_y]

       -type  {manufacturing  |  inst  | placement | userdefine | layertrack |
       finfetInst |finfetmanufacturing | finfetplacement}

       Gets information on the current snap grid settings.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes the type  and  default
              information  for  each  get_snap_grid_info  parameter. For a de-
              tailed description of the command and all of its parameters, use
              the man command:

               man get_snap_grid_info

       -origin
              Specify to get the original point of the grid.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -pitch_x
              Specify to get the X-direction pitch of the grid.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -pitch_y
              Specify to get the Y-direction pitch of the grid.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -type {manufacturing | inst | placement | userdefine | layertrack |
       finfetInst |finfetmanufacturing | finfetplacement}
              Specify the grid type for which the information is required. The
              grid types can be:

              * manufacturing: Manufacture Grid

              * inst: Instance Grid

              * placement: Placement Grid

              * userDefine: User-defined Grid

              * LayerTrack: LayerTrack Grid

              * finfetManufacturing: FinFET Manufacture Grid

              * finfetInst: FinFET Instance Grid

              * finfetPlacement: FinFET Placement Grid

              Data_type: enum, required

Examples
       The following commands displays the snap grid settings for  the  place-
       ment grid:

       get_snap_grid_info -type placement

       For example:

       {origin  {0.0000000000,0.0000000000}}  {pitch_x  0.6600000000} {pitch_y
       0.5600000000}

Related Information
